                    <BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD>Ive been reading from the start  but i didnt know how to post but now im here <BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />Grieves,Vanda Darkflame's Boyfreind </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />plz read my upcoming book power of five and plz let me use majorq12 as one of the five </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />I've actually talked to some of my readers about this, and I'm afraid the answer is no.  I reserve all rights to The Major, the kids, and the Legend of Crux (including its soundtrack <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />)<BR /><BR />But no, being serious, there are certain things (most of which connect to his past) that I have not revealed yet, and am planning to do in this story, possibly very soon.  While it's thrilling to see how much you like the Major, I'm afraid that for the moment use of him is off-limits.  <BR /><BR />However, if you can show me that I can trust you to use him well (meaning he only does what I believe he would do in any particular situation) and write with grammar and clarity that meet my standards, then I'll consider it.  No sooner.<BR /><BR /><BR />A short note to all readers:  Those three posts from me in a row were made tuesday, but they didn't get up until today.  The Mods were giving me a hard time, and I HOPE it won't happen again <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR /><BR />Till then, read on!<BR /><BR />~~The Original Major~~ </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />Well, I guess I can see why everybody likes him. He's a really interesting and dynamic character, no wonder several people want him in their stories. And, unfortunately, as I read that, I realised that there is a very Major-ish spot to fill in my story.<img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR />But wait! You said that you reserve the rights of the kids, but, in asking to have Axolc put in the story, does that mean that you reserve rights for him? Wouldn't I still have a share in the reservation, character wise? And out of the five main characters, would't I technically own a fifth of them? would it work as an exchange, with me giving you Axolc and you giving me Major? Or would I just get a fifth of any character (If it's the second, I'm stuck between The Major's Helmet, or his shoes<img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />) Or does this not work at all? <BR />Anyway, *Legal* business aside, I wonder what the Majors past is. Did he once do something to Vylar, or vice-versa? What happened to Jonathon's childhood? What happened to Axolc memory about the transport. What is the A.N.C.C.H thing(Did I get that right?<img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />) And finally, yes, I will be reading on!<img class="emoticon emoticon-thumbs_up" id="thumbs_up" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/thumbsUp.png" alt="Thumbs up" title="Thumbs up" /><BR />XerxesTortugas  <BR />Axolc<BR />"Blarg" </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />...I never thought of that <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /> I really can't reserve the right to you, now can I? <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />  If you used yourself in a story... well... idk, as faithful to this story as you've been, I must remain consistant.  I guess we could just say that the Axolc in your story is in a parallel (Lego) Universe where he is not assosiated to the Major.  Beyond that, I have no clue <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR /><BR />~~The Original Major~~
                
            
			
