                    <BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD>Ok first off i have to say this is THE best topic i have EVER read PEIROD!!!!! I am one of your biggest admierers. The reason i like you is because you are not a jerk like a lot of people on the boards you are actually a nice guy. You even inspiered me to write my own story called MYTHRAN ORIGINS which i will be posting soon. I wanted to ask if i could use something from your story.Now i know about how you feel and what you'v about the major so ill respect that and not use or ask to use him. I wanted to know if i could go more into detail about the "gift" the first builders gave to the people of crux, you see my guys name is called Mythran Stone and he finds out in my story that he has something called "imagination" in his blood and he finds this out by the voices of the great builders he hears. It would help my story a lot and i wouldnt change a thing on how the people of crux got there or any thing else thet you wrote about i just want to tie something to the "gift". i would also would reference them to your story because it would be connected with mine. Please concider this and let me know what you think.<BR /><BR />                                            Yours truly, starwars7495 aka Lightninwarrior95.<BR /><BR /><BR />~Life is a lego set, open the possibilities~ </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />The "gift"?  The gift is the Imgaination Nexus <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />  I'll be getting into that a bit more later on.  I also have (SPOILER ALERT!!) a plan in place for the Mythrans, but that shouldn't stop you from writing your own (END SPOILER ALERT) <img class="emoticon emoticon-happy" id="happy" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/happy.png" alt="Happy" title="Happy" /> that's one of the things I love about this forum: everyone has their own rules and stories for whatever the game left out, so there are nearly infinite different continuities to choose from! <img class="emoticon emoticon-happy" id="happy" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/happy.png" alt="Happy" title="Happy" />  If you want to connect your story with mine, I would advice you to wait until I've revealed more about the concerned things, but that's up to you.  I won't blame you if you decide not to, because it may take a while for me to cover this stuff, but if you decide not to wait you just run the risk of splitting into your own continuity (not that there's anything wrong with that <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />)<BR /><BR /><BR />Now I noticed that some readers (although I'm hoping most of them are but just haven't said it) have been getting excited wondering about the mystery side of Crux Origins.  Well, all I am going to say is, at least for some of these secrets, there's not much time left to wait...<BR /><BR />...But on a related note, things have been getting pretty busy on my end, and that + slow moderation preventing adequate flow of information = high probability of increased waiting time before I can release the next chapter.  Believe me, I wish I could spend more time writing this, but it can't be helped <img class="emoticon emoticon-sad" id="sad" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/sad.png" alt="Sad" title="Sad" /><BR /><BR />Judging from the current pattern, by the time this gets approved it will probably be out of date <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR /><BR />~~The Original Major~~
                
            
			
