				<p class="lia-message-dates lia-message-post-date lia-component-post-date-last-edited" class="lia-message-dates lia-message-post-date">
					
		 <span class="DateTime lia-message-posted-on lia-component-common-widget-date" class="DateTime lia-message-posted-on">
    

	
		
		
		<span class="local-date">‎02-07-2012</span>
	
		
		<span class="local-time">06:04 PM</span>
	
	

	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
</span>
	
				</p>
			
		
			
				
						
		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_11" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    ok, a few things I need to clarify/make official to all readers (I have said these before, but I just want to make sure you understood and an official announcement seemed like the best way):<BR /><BR />First of all, The cross-kit contest I had a while back is over, but I will be using some of my favorites that were submitted earlier.  I will not announce the winners, since they're pretty much the same two or three people, but you'll see which ones I liked as I put them in the story.  But this doesn't mean you shouldn't feel free to post ideas for more.  <img class="emoticon emoticon-smile" id="smile" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/smile.png" alt="Smile" title="Smile" /><BR /><BR /><BR />Secondly, I cannot accept any character requests unless you are willing to have them as an original crux inhabitant (i.e.: from the past, not the future).  This means in your bio, if you have one, you must include which race the character is from (and this does apply even if you don't have a bio).  <BR /><BR />I have not yet determined how to approach the leader of the Mosaic Jesters, so that slot is open if you act fast.  The Bat King has a personallity, but no name, so that is open as far as that goes.  As for the other peoples, the bones have no leader (not "no leader" as in the slot is open, but "no leader" as in they literally have no leader according to my plan <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />).  As far as the Exploreian Bots, I have their leader's personality planned, and a name I can change if necessary.  Please note that if you want one of these you must be fast, but I am flexible enough to add non-leaders of the tribes to the cast, in fact I need them. <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />  So long as they are not from the present, I should be able to make it work.<BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />Lastly:<BR /><BR /><BR />YOU MAY NOT use the Major in your own stories.  It makes me thrilled to see how many people like him, but that doesn't mean you shouldn't be making your own characters without stealing mine.  Feel free to be inspired, but not to steal.  <BR /><BR />I have three good reasons why: <BR />1. The Major is my character, and I just don't like to see him being used without my permission;  <BR />2. I don't want him to be misused or see him doing things which I know he would never do (and yes, Greves, I'm looking at you and your "Nexus Force got a call from the Major");  <BR />3. I have not yet released anything about his past or some secrets about him which I will only hint at in the story, not outside.  You never heard me say that btw <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR /><BR /><BR />At least for now, the same thing applies to the Legend of Crux.  My reason for this is, like the Major, I purposefully left holes so that I could fill them in as the story progressed (that's why they're in the past, remember?).  <BR /><BR />Now, sometimes I may give permission to use this; for example, starwars7495 has my permission to write according to the guidlines he gave in his post, and this is half-because he knows how I feel <img class="emoticon emoticon-smile" id="smile" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/smile.png" alt="Smile" title="Smile" />  But I want anyone, even and especially those who get my permission to use it, to remember this: Almost every word in the opening has meaning, and I will be covering every one that does (except maybe the part about aqua magna and bara magna, for obvious reasons  <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />).<BR /><BR />That said, once this story is finished I will allow the use of The Legend in other peoples stories, I just don't want them writing about it before I can draw an adequate picture.  <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />  <BR /><BR /><BR />These may seem strict, or they may seem unfair, or they may seem justified.  Whatever you think of them, just know that I'm doing this mainly because I don't want to spoil the mystery component of this story <img class="emoticon emoticon-smile" id="smile" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/smile.png" alt="Smile" title="Smile" />  <BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />Got all that?  Good, now I'm one step closer to being able to continue writing <img class="emoticon emoticon-smile" id="smile" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/smile.png" alt="Smile" title="Smile" /><BR /><BR />~~The Original Major~~
                
            
			
				<div style="width:98%; max-height:100px; overflow:hidden;" class="UserSignature lia-message-signature">
	~~The Original Major~~<BR />"The [^ is a lie!"
